WEBVTT

00:01.016 --> 00:04.183
(soft dramatic music)

00:13.205 --> 00:15.836
(birds singing)

00:15.836 --> 00:19.003
(soft dramatic music)

01:48.294 --> 01:50.503
- Oh my gosh, are you okay?

01:50.503 --> 01:53.670
(soft dramatic music)

01:55.592 --> 01:56.675
Are you hurt?

01:57.789 --> 01:59.293
What happened? Are you okay?

02:00.190 --> 02:03.357
(soft dramatic music)

02:10.360 --> 02:12.160
We're gonna get you some help, okay?

02:13.298 --> 02:15.423
(soft dramatic music)

02:15.423 --> 02:17.640
I was just jogging right off the highway.

02:17.640 --> 02:21.023
I found this boy. Please send someone.

02:21.023 --> 02:24.190
(soft dramatic music)

02:28.118 --> 02:29.158
I was just running.

02:29.158 --> 02:31.075
- What's going on here?

02:32.881 --> 02:35.142
What's your name, young man?

02:35.142 --> 02:38.389
(soft dramatic music)

02:38.389 --> 02:40.442
Do you know who you are?

02:40.442 --> 02:43.776
(speaking indistinctly)

02:59.209 --> 03:02.042
(switch clicking)

03:06.474 --> 03:09.952
(soft dramatic music)

03:09.952 --> 03:12.619
(glass humming)

03:18.553 --> 03:20.720
(banging)

03:21.940 --> 03:25.273
(footsteps approaching)

03:26.410 --> 03:28.050
- What do you have, dog ears?

03:28.050 --> 03:29.124
You're gonna have to--

03:29.124 --> 03:30.790
- Your cash is in here too.

03:30.790 --> 03:32.433
- Okay, well, see you tomorrow?

03:37.350 --> 03:39.765
- Ella, unmute my phone,
play my voicemails.

03:39.765 --> 03:40.740
- [Ella] Voicemail, one.

03:40.740 --> 03:41.640
- [John] Hey, it's John.

03:41.640 --> 03:43.137
The marketing meeting was moved up a week,

03:43.137 --> 03:44.579
and our deadline right along with it,

03:44.579 --> 03:47.070
so we're gonna need the
tuning fork recordings pronto.

03:47.070 --> 03:49.730
It's critical we get
those demo videos ready.

03:49.730 --> 03:50.770
Call me.

03:50.770 --> 03:51.603
- Delete.

03:51.603 --> 03:53.450
- [Ella] Deleted, voicemail two.

03:53.450 --> 03:55.430
- [Barb] Hi, this is Barb Wilson.

03:55.430 --> 03:58.010
Max said that you are
the sounds effects guy.

03:58.010 --> 04:00.279
I have a project that
needs your expertise.

04:00.279 --> 04:01.112
- Save.

04:01.112 --> 04:02.780
- [Ella] Saved, voicemail three.

04:02.780 --> 04:04.633
- [Alan] Hey, kid, it's me.

04:05.670 --> 04:09.090
I need closure on this,
and I haven't heard back.

04:09.090 --> 04:10.921
I know you don't like visitors, okay?

04:10.921 --> 04:11.754
- Delete.

04:11.754 --> 04:13.333
- [Ella] Deleted, no more voicemail.

04:14.700 --> 04:17.617
(soft piano music)

04:38.854 --> 04:40.670
- [Alex] Mom?

04:40.670 --> 04:41.503
Mom?

04:42.590 --> 04:43.863
When's dinner?

04:45.250 --> 04:47.560
- [Martha] Trudy picked
up her wedding dress.

04:47.560 --> 04:50.630
The back ripped, and all
the beads, they fell out.

04:50.630 --> 04:52.290
I'm sorry, honey.

04:52.290 --> 04:54.290
She needs it first thing in the morning.

04:56.670 --> 04:58.130
- [Alex] Can we have taquitos?

05:00.440 --> 05:02.870
- [Martha] Listen, honey,
grab some money outta my purse

05:02.870 --> 05:05.200
and run on down to the corner
and get yourself something,

05:05.200 --> 05:06.930
and bring me a, um--

05:06.930 --> 05:08.119
- A Diet Coke.

05:08.119 --> 05:10.452
- [Martha] Diet Coke, okay?

05:10.452 --> 05:11.828
- Poor Trudy.

05:11.828 --> 05:14.332
- [Ella] Window, window.

05:14.332 --> 05:15.788
- Stop the alarm.

05:15.788 --> 05:17.672
- [Ella] Alarm stopped.

05:17.672 --> 05:20.839
(soft dramatic music)

06:04.172 --> 06:07.089
(knocking on door)

06:12.136 --> 06:13.880
- [Winters] Impeccable timing.

06:13.880 --> 06:14.713
- Hey, Boss.

06:14.713 --> 06:17.001
- I told you I'm not your boss.

06:17.001 --> 06:17.834
- Yeah, you are.

06:17.834 --> 06:20.840
Technically, I have over
100 different bosses

06:20.840 --> 06:22.340
in this building.

06:22.340 --> 06:26.210
- But only the miserly
landlord, Harris, pays you.

06:26.210 --> 06:28.740
Therefore, you only have one boss.

06:28.740 --> 06:30.080
- Miserly.

06:30.080 --> 06:32.909
Penny pincher, tightwad, cheapskate.

06:32.909 --> 06:33.743
- Bingo.

06:34.710 --> 06:35.543
- In here?

06:41.411 --> 06:42.970
(soft dramatic music)

06:42.970 --> 06:46.813
Just a small leak, but I fixed it for you.

06:48.830 --> 06:52.140
No, not again, I'll get fired.

06:52.140 --> 06:53.430
- You're not gonna get fired.

06:53.430 --> 06:56.310
I have enough dirt on Harris
that you're safe forever.

06:56.310 --> 07:00.110
- If he finds out, he'll get
so angry. He's vindictive.

07:00.110 --> 07:02.163
- Unforgiving, vengeful?

07:05.300 --> 07:07.390
Suit yourself.

07:07.390 --> 07:09.313
I'll just return it then.

07:10.870 --> 07:14.790
- Does that have a 1983 stamp date

07:15.640 --> 07:18.123
and an inner tray with matching thermos?

07:23.120 --> 07:24.853
No scratches on the edges.

07:25.960 --> 07:28.610
Holographic graphics.

07:28.610 --> 07:32.013
According to my collector's
manual, this one's rare.

07:35.840 --> 07:37.330
Do you want me to put
the bug in the air vent?

07:37.330 --> 07:39.430
- Wherever you think is best. I trust you.

07:41.969 --> 07:44.670
- The new couple, in 102.

07:44.670 --> 07:45.995
Blonde, male, five-foot-10--

07:45.995 --> 07:48.050
- Yeah yeah, I don't care
about all that, okay?

07:48.050 --> 07:49.113
Only how they sound.

07:50.570 --> 07:53.110
- Do you wanna see where
I put my other lunchboxes,

07:53.110 --> 07:54.873
and my poster collection?

07:54.873 --> 07:56.783
- Okay, you know I can't leave this room.

07:58.220 --> 07:59.970
- Because of what's wrong with you?

08:03.000 --> 08:04.100
- Thanks for the sink.

08:07.891 --> 08:11.058
(soft dramatic music)

08:27.115 --> 08:30.397
(footsteps descending)

08:30.397 --> 08:33.563
(soft dramatic music)

08:46.452 --> 08:49.165
(exhaling)

08:49.165 --> 08:51.748
(door closing)

08:56.400 --> 08:58.567
(sighing)

08:59.820 --> 09:00.930
- [Gordon] You know how she is.

09:00.930 --> 09:03.052
- [Becky] She's freaking
out over what happened.

09:03.052 --> 09:04.114
- [Gordon] I'm sure.

09:04.114 --> 09:05.777
- [Becky] Imagining shit
that never happened.

09:05.777 --> 09:07.710
And you know what? She believes it too.

09:07.710 --> 09:10.092
- [Gordon] You're right.
Someone needs to go talk to her.

09:10.092 --> 09:11.730
- [Becky] Yeah, you need to do it.

09:11.730 --> 09:14.030
- Me?
- Yes, you, yes.

09:14.030 --> 09:15.530
- Why can't Manny go talk to her?

09:15.530 --> 09:19.040
- Gordon, you're the only one
with the balls for the job.

09:19.040 --> 09:20.593
Expect Manny to do it?

09:21.720 --> 09:24.850
When's the last time he
did anything worthwhile?

09:24.850 --> 09:26.135
- [Christine] Things are
different between us.

09:26.135 --> 09:27.930
- [Scott] Why do we keep going over this?

09:27.930 --> 09:29.717
- [Christine] Can we just talk about this?

09:29.717 --> 09:30.550
- [Scott] There's this thing at work.

09:30.550 --> 09:32.321
I'm under a lotta stress.

09:32.321 --> 09:33.515
- [Christine] You're being so distant.

09:33.515 --> 09:34.348
- [Scott] If you can't trust me,

09:34.348 --> 09:36.670
that's you sabotaging our relationship.

09:36.670 --> 09:38.573
- Wow, don't let him do that.

09:40.000 --> 09:42.396
Don't apologize. He's cheating
on you, and you know it.

09:42.396 --> 09:43.447
- [Christine] Please--

09:43.447 --> 09:45.025
(knocking on door)

09:45.025 --> 09:46.725
- [Scott] Maybe I should just go.

09:47.726 --> 09:50.309
(upbeat piano music)

09:52.840 --> 09:54.896
- Hey, sorry to interrupt.

09:54.896 --> 09:55.729
- Interrupt what?

09:55.729 --> 09:57.923
- Oh, it sounded like you had company.

09:59.180 --> 10:02.547
Anyway, do you have any
ice? My fridge is out.

10:06.976 --> 10:09.559
(door closing)

10:14.810 --> 10:16.140
- You should have Leonard
check that out for you.

10:16.140 --> 10:17.133
- Check what out?

10:18.430 --> 10:20.390
- Isn't your fridge broke?

10:20.390 --> 10:21.543
- Oh yeah, thanks.

10:22.819 --> 10:23.652
- Rosie?

10:27.824 --> 10:31.741
(upbeat classical piano music)

10:38.415 --> 10:42.415
(muffled shouting through wall)

10:50.816 --> 10:53.983
(soft dramatic music)

10:57.096 --> 10:58.929
- [Shawn] Fucking bitch!

11:00.181 --> 11:02.138
Where did you put my fucking money?

11:02.138 --> 11:04.888
Why do you have to act like this?

11:07.392 --> 11:11.392
(muffled shouting through wall)

11:12.761 --> 11:15.633
You are worthless! You are nothing!

11:15.633 --> 11:19.550
(upbeat classical piano music)

11:28.135 --> 11:31.216
(soft dramatic music)

11:31.216 --> 11:33.490
- [Maggie] Did you get help?

11:33.490 --> 11:35.990
(piano music)

11:42.211 --> 11:44.961
(piano breaking)

11:58.847 --> 12:02.680
(singing in foreign language)

12:51.258 --> 12:54.258
(doorknob jiggling)

13:05.271 --> 13:07.650
- Huh, I love what
you've done to the place.

13:07.650 --> 13:08.660
Did you get my message?

13:08.660 --> 13:11.563
- Yeah, something, something closure.

13:13.240 --> 13:14.790
- Uh, this is, uh--

13:14.790 --> 13:16.270
- Sh.

13:16.270 --> 13:19.053
- This is yours. Marie
wanted you to have it.

13:26.393 --> 13:27.823
Do you wanna see what it is?

13:27.823 --> 13:31.801
- Don't touch that, okay.
Everything has its place.

13:31.801 --> 13:32.634
Okay.

13:36.780 --> 13:39.290
- You know, Marie got sick a year ago.

13:39.290 --> 13:41.480
Four months ago, she
went into the hospital.

13:41.480 --> 13:43.730
Eight weeks ago, I put her in the ground.

13:43.730 --> 13:44.863
Where the hell were you?

13:44.863 --> 13:46.440
- I can't do this right now.

13:46.440 --> 13:48.620
- All that progress and
you just threw it away

13:48.620 --> 13:50.243
when she needed you the most.

13:51.540 --> 13:53.010
I must have been a fool, you know,

13:53.010 --> 13:55.233
to think that maybe you loved her.

13:56.520 --> 13:58.290
Wait wait wait, let me guess.

13:58.290 --> 14:01.100
Because of your retrograde amnesia,

14:01.100 --> 14:04.123
you couldn't remember whether
you gave a damn or not.

14:05.070 --> 14:06.410
You know what?

14:06.410 --> 14:10.363
Now that she's gone, me and
you, we're done, for good.

14:12.340 --> 14:13.173
- Alan?

14:18.235 --> 14:20.280
One of my neighbors, she plays the piano.

14:20.280 --> 14:22.940
She practices every
afternoon from four to six,

14:22.940 --> 14:24.780
except weekends and Saturdays,

14:24.780 --> 14:27.330
she'll play once in the
morning after breakfast

14:27.330 --> 14:28.580
and once at night around six.

14:28.580 --> 14:29.413
Sunday, she plays--

14:29.413 --> 14:30.850
- What do you want?

14:30.850 --> 14:32.000
- Someone destroyed it.

14:33.030 --> 14:35.800
The piano, late last night.

14:35.800 --> 14:39.710
I just need you to go knock on
her door, see if she answers.

14:39.710 --> 14:42.130
And that's all. It's Room 607.

14:42.130 --> 14:44.330
- You're really worried
about your neighbor?

14:46.440 --> 14:49.130
- By this time today, she'd
have practiced already.

14:49.130 --> 14:51.580
She'd be out of the shower,
blow-drying her hair.

14:51.580 --> 14:53.380
- How do you know that?

14:53.380 --> 14:55.250
You know what? Call the cops.

14:55.250 --> 14:56.083
- No.

14:57.340 --> 14:58.240
- Well, great, do it yourself, kid.

14:58.240 --> 15:00.980
- I'd have to leave this
room. I can't do that.

15:00.980 --> 15:02.380
- Whew, bye-bye.

15:02.380 --> 15:03.430
- There's more, okay.

15:04.280 --> 15:07.253
Whoever destroyed it, left this playing.

15:09.462 --> 15:10.990
(operatic singing in foreign language)

15:10.990 --> 15:15.990
Alan, when I heard it, I saw something.

15:17.230 --> 15:20.340
But I didn't just see it, I remembered it.

15:20.340 --> 15:21.393
It was a memory.

15:22.410 --> 15:25.213
I think it was from before
that day Marie found me.

15:26.270 --> 15:29.122
Okay, I need you to go over there.

15:29.122 --> 15:31.343
I just need you to see
what the hell's going on.

15:33.810 --> 15:35.857
- I will not enable you like she did.

15:37.627 --> 15:39.630
And don't expect any more gigs from me,

15:39.630 --> 15:41.520
because from now on I'm using Paul.

15:41.520 --> 15:42.870
- That hack!

15:42.870 --> 15:43.703
- What?

15:44.730 --> 15:47.360
- Fine, fine. Use Paul, I don't care.

15:47.360 --> 15:48.963
But that music.

15:50.700 --> 15:52.073
I saw this door.

15:53.284 --> 15:54.330
- Are you still taking your meds?

15:54.330 --> 15:56.250
- Someone knew I'd be
listening, I know it.

15:56.250 --> 15:59.470
- I said, are you still taking your meds?

15:59.470 --> 16:00.303
- What?

16:00.303 --> 16:01.571
- Not what. Answer me, are
you still taking your meds?

16:01.571 --> 16:02.988
- Yes, yes, I am!

16:03.913 --> 16:08.496
(operatic singing in foreign language)

16:15.067 --> 16:18.515
- Hey hey hey, is this what I think it is?

16:18.515 --> 16:20.060
(soft dramatic music)

16:20.060 --> 16:21.763
These are apartment numbers.

16:22.760 --> 16:26.043
You've been taping your neighbors'
apartments, haven't you?

16:27.720 --> 16:30.930
Just to feed that sick fetish of yours.

16:30.930 --> 16:32.760
That's how you know what
the hell they're up to.

16:32.760 --> 16:34.800
- They may not be relationships to you,

16:34.800 --> 16:37.863
but to me, they are my family.

16:38.963 --> 16:39.820
- Huh.

16:39.820 --> 16:42.100
Wow, hey I'm really happy

16:42.100 --> 16:44.310
that you're surrounded by your family,

16:44.310 --> 16:46.840
while the woman who devoted
her goddam life to you

16:46.840 --> 16:48.910
wasted away and died!

16:48.910 --> 16:50.840
Hey, news flash, kid.

16:50.840 --> 16:52.350
They're not your family.

16:52.350 --> 16:54.890
They don't know who you
are, and they don't care.

16:54.890 --> 16:56.490
- Okay, okay, thanks for stopping by, Dad.

16:56.490 --> 16:59.913
- I'm not your dad, and
Marie was not your mother.

17:01.070 --> 17:03.720
As much as she tried to be
when she brought you home.

17:04.589 --> 17:06.140
She did everything to help you,

17:07.890 --> 17:10.060
including sacrificing us.

17:10.060 --> 17:14.343
(operatic singing in foreign language)

17:14.343 --> 17:15.403
You know what?

17:16.579 --> 17:19.623
You belong in a psych ward,
just like your real mother.

17:21.140 --> 17:22.454
Don't call me.

17:22.454 --> 17:27.038
(operatic signing in foreign language)

17:30.468 --> 17:33.540
- [Ella] Incoming call from John.

17:33.540 --> 17:34.600
- Answer.

17:34.600 --> 17:35.690
- [John] Hello.

17:35.690 --> 17:36.523
- I'm here.

17:36.523 --> 17:38.360
- [John] Did you get yesterday's message?

17:38.360 --> 17:40.750
Our editor needs the tuning
fork sound effects right away.

17:40.750 --> 17:43.470
It's a product video. We
can't go canned on it.

17:43.470 --> 17:45.670
- You moved up the
deadline. There's a queue.

17:45.670 --> 17:49.549
- [John] I'm prepared to pay
triple. Are you onboard or not?

17:49.549 --> 17:50.983
- Yeah, yeah, I'm onboard.

17:58.728 --> 18:01.702
(soft dramatic music)

18:01.702 --> 18:04.285
(fork humming)

18:08.286 --> 18:11.453
(soft dramatic music)

18:14.013 --> 18:16.094
- [Maggie] Hey.

18:16.094 --> 18:18.844
(dramatic music)

18:23.062 --> 18:25.812
(hard breathing)

18:27.440 --> 18:28.730
- [Winters] Ella, call John.

18:28.730 --> 18:30.566
- [Ella] Calling John.

18:30.566 --> 18:31.400
(phone ringing)

18:31.400 --> 18:32.370
- [John] Hello.

18:32.370 --> 18:35.286
- Your client with the
tuning forks, who is it?

18:35.286 --> 18:37.313
- [John] I'm sorry, but once again?

18:38.500 --> 18:40.210
- Who are we making the recordings for?

18:40.210 --> 18:41.823
Who hired you to make the video?

18:44.620 --> 18:47.230
I don't even see a brand on this product.

18:47.230 --> 18:49.030
What kind of tuning forks are these?

18:51.060 --> 18:52.253
Is this a real gig?

18:55.500 --> 18:56.863
Who hired you to call me?

18:57.864 --> 18:59.531
- [Ella] Call ended.

19:09.442 --> 19:12.359
(knocking on door)

19:15.929 --> 19:19.090
- I haven't gone into
102 yet. I was waiting--

19:19.090 --> 19:19.923
- The piano player in 607,

19:19.923 --> 19:22.230
have you seen her since yesterday?

19:22.230 --> 19:24.752
- No, I haven't seen her in over a month.

19:24.752 --> 19:25.620
- A month?

19:25.620 --> 19:28.830
- Yeah, her window was stuck,
so I stuck in my putty knife,

19:28.830 --> 19:29.740
and then with my hammer I--

19:29.740 --> 19:31.050
- Something's wrong.

19:31.050 --> 19:33.520
I didn't wanna ask you, but
you have to go check on her.

19:33.520 --> 19:35.420
Okay, you have to see
if something happened.

19:35.420 --> 19:38.230
- Whoa, um, is she sick?

19:38.230 --> 19:40.709
Because like Dr. Lee, in 702, maybe he--

19:40.709 --> 19:42.663
- No, she's not sick. She's ...

19:44.870 --> 19:46.313
I heard that ...

19:47.330 --> 19:48.163
There's this ...

19:53.150 --> 19:54.993
I'm sending you on a mission.

19:56.510 --> 19:58.600
I'm sending you on a mission.

19:58.600 --> 20:01.570
I'm the boss, okay, the sergeant,

20:01.570 --> 20:05.780
and you, you're the soldier
carrying out the mission.

20:05.780 --> 20:07.533
- You're not making any sense.

20:17.780 --> 20:19.947
- [Winters] Testing, can you hear me?

20:19.947 --> 20:22.050
Testing.

20:22.050 --> 20:23.380
- Hello, hello.

20:23.380 --> 20:25.490
- Private, this is a recon mission, okay.

20:25.490 --> 20:28.010
You're gonna go to Room
607, and you are gonna

20:28.010 --> 20:29.600
report back to me what you see

20:29.600 --> 20:31.200
through this, do you understand?

20:32.300 --> 20:33.133
Go.

20:34.290 --> 20:36.196
Where are you right now?

20:36.196 --> 20:39.103
- [Leonard] Okay, I'm here, Room 607.

20:40.090 --> 20:41.510
- Is there anything out of the ordinary?

20:41.510 --> 20:42.910
Do you see anybody?

20:42.910 --> 20:46.493
- [Leonard] I don't see
anybody. It kinda smells funny.

20:48.120 --> 20:50.203
It's unlocked. Should I go in?

20:52.480 --> 20:54.557
Hello, should I go in?

20:54.557 --> 20:56.913
- Yeah, slowly, don't touch anything.

20:57.843 --> 21:00.690
(door creaking)

21:00.690 --> 21:02.390
- [Leonard] It smells bad in here.

21:03.873 --> 21:05.033
- What do you see?

21:07.340 --> 21:11.310
- [Leonard] It's dark. The
light switch doesn't work.

21:11.310 --> 21:12.860
- Use your flashlight, Leonard.

21:15.070 --> 21:16.353
- [Leonard] I'm scared.

21:17.240 --> 21:18.693
- That's an order, Private.

21:20.599 --> 21:22.120
- [Leonard] Okay.

21:22.120 --> 21:23.270
- Tell me what you see.

21:25.880 --> 21:28.113
- [Leonard] There's plastic everywhere.

21:29.120 --> 21:30.066
- Plastic?

21:30.066 --> 21:33.050
(dramatic music)

21:33.050 --> 21:36.840
Get out. Leonard, Leonard,
Leonard, get out of there now!

21:36.840 --> 21:38.840
- [Leonard] Oh my God. Pieces!

21:38.840 --> 21:41.387
- The piano, the piano's in pieces?

21:41.387 --> 21:45.387
- Blood, there's blood (cries).

21:47.659 --> 21:49.826
I am in trouble, aren't I?

